cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.SC 

The paper deals with techniques for proving termination of graph transformation systems, which is a topic related to logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of matrix interpretations and semirings also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and formal languages (cs.FL). Finally, the implementation of the techniques in the tool Grez suggests a possible connection to scientific computing (cs.SC).
